Information
------------------------------

Inside Jaguar: Making a Million Pound Car
Presented by classic car fanatic, Mark Evans, the film follows Jaguar during the production of the elite vehicle known as the Lightweight, an exact recreation of the racing version of the iconic E-Type. But however rich you are, you can't just buy one of these cars - you must be chosen. Six individuals have been hand-picked by Jaguar to own one. 
Only twelve Lightweights were ever made, back in 1963, one of which recently sold for an estimated Ãƒâ€šÃ‚Â£5 million. But eighteen were originally planned and now the remaining six are being recreated by Jaguar from scratch with precision engineering. 
With access to Jaguar's production line and wealthy owners of both original and new Lightweights, this film will explore the love of classic cars and what drives people to shell out huge sums of money for them.
